place.name: HANLEY WILLIAM
place.gazetteerText: HANLEY-WILLIAM, or UPPER HANLEY, a parish in Tenbury district, Worcester; adjacent to Herefordshire, and near the river Teme, 6 miles SE of Tenbury r. station. Post town, Tenbury. Acres, 1, 155. Pop., 120. Houses, 26. The living is a rectory, annexed to the rectory of Eastham, in the diocese of Hereford. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
